</blockquote>

<p>The concluding stanza is inferior to the others and suffers by comparison with the excellent lines of Miss Winkworth cited above: it is a very free paraphrase and leaves the impression of having been hastily constructed:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>As each short year goes quickly round,<br />
Our hallelujahs shall resound;<br />
And when we reckon years no more,<br />
May we in heaven thy name adore!</p>
</blockquote>

